    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available is a driver-focused 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine with individual throttle bodies and a 7,900 RPM redline. This example is equipped with the desirable 6-speed Getrag manual transmission and a factory M-Variable differential lock. The mechanicals are robust: the dual-VANOS system has been serviced, and the rear subframe has been proactively reinforced to ensure structural rigidity under lateral load. Suspension remains tight with refreshed bushings and MacPherson struts. While showing honest patina consistent with a well-maintained driver, the powertrain delivers linear torque and that signature metallic rasp. A mechanically sound, analog performance icon ready for the twisties.",
